cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.CV

This paper proposes a method for improving fairness in machine learning algorithms, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves manipulating the data to remove correlations between protected variables, which could also fall under the sub-field of computer ethics (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper discusses the interpretability of the resulting features, which could relate to the sub-field of cryptography (cs.CR) in terms of ensuring transparency and accountability in algorithmic decision-making.
